description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WORCESTERSHIRE HEALTHY MINDS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IMPROVING ACCESS TO PSYCHOLOGICAL THERAPIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BASED AT THE WULSTAN UNIT, WORCESTER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SENIOR PSYCHOLOGICAL WELLBEING PRACTITIONER&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BAND 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 HOURS PER WEEK x 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a dynamic and highly motivated and skilled individual who will complement our IAPT service.  The post holder will be expected to provide clinical leadership to a team of PWPs and PWP trainees who provide triage and step 2 interventions based on CBT for the treatment of mild to moderate depression and anxiety disorders.  Our low intensity interventions are delivered via a combination of course, telephone, digital and face to face treatment sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service is looking for someone who has a keen interest in clinical effectiveness and quality and in developing course and digital provision to meet growing demand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to provide case management and clinical skills supervision as well as take part in training the PWP workforce within the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to working alongside colleagues you will be required to carry out individual assessments and deliver step 2 interventions to patients with low to moderate mental health difficulties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the role you will be expected to work flexibly to suit the needs of the service, this may include early or late evening appointments/co-facilitating groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PREVIOUS APPLICANTS NEED NOT APPLY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have the ambition to be part of a highly successful team and wish to discuss the role further, you are welcome to contact Jo Salt Senior PWP / Step 2 Lead on 01562 828829.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;All staff whatever their role, level or responsibility will be encouraged and supported to do their job well and to improve their job.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Making Every Day Better for patients, staff, service users and carers is the responsibility of all of us and we want to embed a culture within the organisation that encourages and supports the drive to improve what we do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
